headline: BofA says history shows no penalty for buying S&P 500 at all-time highs
summary: Investing.com -- Bank of America said in a note Thursday that investors should not fear buying U.S. equities at record levels, noting that “over the past fifty years, S&P 500 returns showed no penalty versus buying on any other occasion, and five years later there was on average a meaningful boost.”
